<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/42432349-saraeliza"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1441808921i/42432349._UX100_CR0,16,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/42432349-saraeliza">SaraEliza</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I agree with Richard. Not strictly necessary, but the read is richer for taking them in order. I also found that my brain placed the historical contex<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I agree with Richard. Not strictly necessary, but the read is richer for taking them in order. I also found that my brain placed the historical context more vividly than if I were reading randomly.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
